            <title>[CASSANDRA-1317] StorageProxy ignores snitch when determining whether to do a local read</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1317</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;this primarily affects &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1314&quot; title=&quot;snitch that prefers a single replica for all reads to a given key&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-1314&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-1314&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and to a lesser degree &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-981&quot; title=&quot;Dynamic endpoint snitch&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-981&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-981&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
